1 SECTION 5. IC 12-14-30-9.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
2 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 9.5. (a) As used in this section,
4 "accessory food":
5 (1) means accessory food items excluded from the definition
6 of "staple food" under 7 CFR 271.2; and
7 (2) includes the following:
8 (A) An energy drink.
9 (B) A sweetened beverage.
10 (C) A soft drink.
11 (D) Corn or potato chips.
12 (E) Prepared desserts, including:
13 (i) cookies;
14 (ii) candy;
15 (iii) ice cream;
16 (iv) cakes; and
17 (v) pies.
18 (b) As used in this section, "energy drink" means a beverage
19 that:
20 (1) contains at least sixty-five (65) milligrams of caffeine per
21 eight (8) fluid ounces; and
22 (2) is advertised or marketed as being specifically designed to
23 provide metabolic stimulation or an increase to the
24 consumer's mental or physical energy.
25 (c) As used in this section, "soft drink" means a carbonated
26 beverage to which sugar or an artificial sweetener has been added.
27 (d) As used in this section, "sweetened beverage" means a
28 nonalcoholic beverage:
29 (1) to which a natural or artificial sweetener is added; and
30 (2) that is sold for human consumption;
31 including a soft drink and other flavored beverages.
32 (e) The following apply with regards to SNAP benefits:
33 (1) Except as provided in subsection (f), a SNAP recipient may
34 not use SNAP benefits to purchase an accessory food.
35 (2) A SNAP recipient may use SNAP benefits to purchase hot
36 prepared chicken that is not fried or breaded, such as
37 rotisserie chicken or grilled chicken fingers.
38 (f) This section does not apply to the following:
39 (1) A milk product or a product, other than a soft drink or
40 energy drink, containing milk or milk protein.
41 (2) A milk substitute, including soy milk, rice milk, or almond
42 milk.
